Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.33,0:00:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother abandoned you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.90,0:00:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You were thrown away like trash\Nalong with your drunken father!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come out of\Nthe trash dump again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.69,0:02:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I'm going to\Nhave to ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.76,0:02:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to drink,\Ndo it after you pay your tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.63,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's money...\NHere. This is for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have drinks to be bought\Nwith money earned by children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.93,0:02:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean what happened\Nto Mr. Conrad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.78,0:02:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Hillman's dog, too.\NCould it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.62,0:02:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have the guts\Nto shoot a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.62,0:02:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a drunk coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to\Nbe searching, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Merkel, let's call it a day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Merkel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.49,0:03:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I found him ! I found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Merkel ! Merâ€“
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.44,0:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Merkel...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.02,0:03:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Laufer!\NPlease respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone !\NSomeone answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also going to\Ntake your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He doesn't have the guts\Nto shoot a gun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.49,0:04:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.49,0:04:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's just a drunk coward.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Across town, there\Nare countless corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.76,0:05:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.80,0:05:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Wim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NCalm down. It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.\NNow let go of the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really remember.\NI shot them, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They were teasing me...\Nso I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.48,0:06:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Calm down. It's all right.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down. Try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.76,0:06:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did you get this gun from?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Laufer, I'm surprised you\Ngot this far on that leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Call the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The telephone doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,M-My gun was taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.64,0:06:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By someone in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.81,0:06:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. He was an outsider\NI've never seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.42,0:06:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, apply first aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.82,0:06:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he one of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you\Nhave come to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.67,0:06:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You've scattered quite\Na few guns around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.54,0:07:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You've even given\Nthis child a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.08,0:07:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A gun? Did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.71,0:07:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're not trash."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Don't bother with them."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.98,0:07:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"You were born for a reason."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You told him those things\Nto encourage him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't shoot the gun.\NAll the bullets are still in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.17,0:07:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim did just what\Nyou taught him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way,\Nthis town is filled with corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.89,0:08:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How many guns did you\Nhand out in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.47,0:08:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people\Ngot guns from you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.77,0:08:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me any angrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.78,0:08:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Something terrible will happen\Nif you make me angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked just like\Nour grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked just like\Nour dead grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.62,0:08:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.09,0:08:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew us well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if he was\Nour real grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You were writing a letter\Nto your dead grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You were sending\Nhim information.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.81,0:08:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he's after.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mr. Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:09:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Franz...Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The heavy rain that continues\Nto fall in southern Germany{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.47,0:09:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has caused many casualties\Nalong the rivers in Bavaria.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you smoke too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. I've quit drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.71,0:09:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You should quit smoking, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.38,0:09:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what have you\Nbeen drawing all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NDoes it look like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.06,0:09:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Look like whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to give that\Nto the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.53,0:09:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't believe you\Nat the crucial moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.80,0:09:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll tell them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm talking about this man."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"This man has gone off\Nto hunt monsters by himself."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.25,0:09:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma's going to\Ncome back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, a report on the damage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Due to the Elgar River\Nflooding,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}roads have been\Nclosed in several areas.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Both outbound and inbound railways\Nhave been shut down.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Also, it's become\Ndiff cult to get calls through{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to areas that have\Nexperienced power failures.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.60,0:10:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an e-mail that\Ncame three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.20,0:10:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After talking to Dr. Gillen, we decided\Nthat we should show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please show it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Nina..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll be waiting for you\Nin Ruhenheim."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.52,0:10:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.19,0:10:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You described what Johan is trying\Nto do right now as "a perfect suicide."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.54,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that lots of innocent people\Nare going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.54,0:10:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruhenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.34,0:11:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a rural village with\Nthat name in southern Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility that\NTenma has headed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.88,0:11:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.99,0:11:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is an odd feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, you were someone who\Nexisted in a certain man's delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.57,0:11:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You were like a character\Nin one of your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've carried out my investigation\Nby compiling objective data.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.25,0:11:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time, I ignored all my data\Nand followed that man's delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.52,0:11:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As I tugged at the loose ends,\Npartially for fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a young man\Nin the Czech Republic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who visited Red Rose Mansion\Nvery often.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.70,0:11:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.33,0:11:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a handwritten postcard\Nthat was sent to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.90,0:12:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's signed K. P. for Klaus Poppe,\Nyour real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.21,0:12:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I've arrived at this place\Nand you're right before my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it still feels odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if a character from\Na picture book has sprung out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.62,0:12:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.99,0:12:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The list of Czech refugees in\Nthe late 80s that I looked up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.96,0:12:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,included the name\NKlaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.83,0:12:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You fled here after\Nthe fall of the Berlin Wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.97,0:12:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you\Ntrying to run from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.94,0:12:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.14,0:12:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,511 Kinderheim was established\Nbecause of your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was created there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you trying to run\Nfrom people like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.42,0:12:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what he. ..what the young man\Nnamed Johan is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.66,0:13:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's happening in\Nthis town right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There were lots of dead people\Non the way to this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.58,0:13:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened\Nto this town?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me out of\Nthis town already!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't right now.\NAll transportation has been cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez. What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You go out and come back and\Ntake a shower each time you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The town smells of gunpowder\Nand blood. It's sickening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.34,0:13:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now calm down. I've ordered\Nhot tea from the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is going to disappear\Nwhen the rain stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"Disappear"? What will?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.13,0:14:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All the memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.03,0:14:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I will let you go\Non two conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You must go with Dr. Gillen...\NAnd you cannot bring a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.52,0:14:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.28,0:14:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And. ..do what I told you\Nto do immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.12,0:14:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, Eva, you Dr. Reichwein,\NMr. Schuwald, Karl and Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.03,0:14:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone that knows Johan\Nmust go into hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is trying to erase\Nall his memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.11,0:14:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.\NTry not to let Dieter see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.49,0:15:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories with Dieter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.39,0:15:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories with you\NDr. Reichwein...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.82,0:15:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories with\NLotte and Karl...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories with\Nthe Fortners...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.66,0:15:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories with\NTenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.87,0:15:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have memories\NI don't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.80,0:15:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I have memories\NI want to erase...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.34,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is. ..\NJohan's memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.48,0:15:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...shouldn't be erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.10,0:15:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A police officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.03,0:15:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,His gun's been taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move from that spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Save this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who shot you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been gunfights\Nall over town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.23,0:16:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,First.. .several armed men\Ncame in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.63,0:16:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, the townspeople had\Nguns and were shooting at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.34,0:16:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go and call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to at least\Nsave the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.78,0:16:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.09,0:16:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.63,0:16:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I heard\Nthat name was in 1995,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.20,0:17:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the statement of\Na certain neurosurgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.67,0:17:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You admit that your deduction\Nis now incorrect?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.74,0:17:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.68,0:17:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still a key witness to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is still just a fabrication.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.12,0:17:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Fabrication"... I was obsessed by\Nthis term throughout my vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.26,0:17:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a person who actually\Nexists have to do to become a fabrication?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.50,0:17:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.47,0:17:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Erase everyone who knows him and\Neveryone who knows about his past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.21,0:17:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, Mr. Bonaparta, it'll be just\Nlike the ending of your picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.72,0:17:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"At last he had\Nfound a name"'
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"but there was no longer anyone\Naround to call him by it."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.85,0:17:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Because Johan is such\Na wonderful name."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.33,0:18:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what's going to\Nhappen to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd do if I were Johan.\NI'm also a fabrication.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.74,0:18:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Newmeyer, the man\Nwhose name is written in the ledger,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.64,0:18:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nor am I Wolfgang Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.11,0:18:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I am nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll disappear with the person who\Ntook my memories and my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.99,0:18:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here\Nfor my verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.67,0:18:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not afraid to die. But I don't\Nknow how to make amends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.51,0:18:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will accept everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not afraid to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how terrible\Nthe things you did were?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.92,0:19:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what it means to destroy\Nthe root of good and evil in a person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what happens when\Nyou awaken the monster within people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,People... People should think\Nthat meals taste good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.47,0:19:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They should look forward\Nto picnics on weekends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.57,0:19:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They should think that a beer\Nafter work tastes good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.55,0:19:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People should...\NPeople should...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.18,0:19:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,feel sad from the bottom of\Ntheir hearts if their child dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get you\Nout of this town safely
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.19,0:19:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and have you make\Neverything public.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to\Nreveal to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.10,0:19:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the identity of the monster\Nthat you awakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.70,0:19:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, I'll protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's behind this massacre.\NWhere is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.13,0:20:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.67,0:20:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is someone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. I'm not holding anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.53,0:20:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.43,0:20:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to help you. Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:21:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous here, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.71,0:21:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.31,0:21:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry! I'll take you to\Nthe path through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.18,0:21:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can run, can't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.42,0:21:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-There's a man giving orders\Nfrom the Hotel Bergbach.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.16,0:21:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.10,0:21:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so,\NI only have this single gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,These two were outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.60,0:21:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This all happened because\NI won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.44,0:21:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If only we had informed the police\Nearlier that we found Conrad's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.91,0:21:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the town\Ngot this crazy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought these?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.89,0:21:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I haven't fired a single shot!\NIt's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me borrow this one\Nand this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.80,0:21:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You protect this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.03,0:21:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even ordinary citizens\Nare carrying guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a detective.\NI can tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah. Mr. Grimmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.31,0:22:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me buy you a beer\Nwhen this job is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, please...a good beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.86,0:22:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.16,0:22:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.46,0:22:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to survive!
